  "text": "The main function of LYP protein would be to downregulate T cells through TCR signaling, by direct effect on dephosphorylation of the protein kinases Lck and Fyn, from complex TCR /CD3 and ZAP70 protein among others (Figure 2) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . It is noteworthy that, according to the genotype of PTPN22 and the two alleles of LYP (LYP * W620 or LYP * R620), a distinct TCR signaling takes place [CITATION_4] .",
